    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; 7 Engine Service Manual - Cylinder Head and Valve Train - Installation
        - Glow Plug Sleeves
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s10.4.2" svcproctype="install" graphiccount="2">
        <title>Glow Plug Sleeves</title>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To prevent personal injury or death, wear safety glasses with side shields. Limit compressed air
                    pressure to 207 kPa (30 psi).
                </para>
            </warning>
            <note>
                <para>Make sure the glow plug recess was cleaned out with the
                    <hotlnk document="eges3451_237.xml" xrefid="s10.t3">Glow Plug Sleeve Seat Wire Brush ZTSE4589
                    </hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="s10.t3"/>, rinsed with a suitable cleaning solution, and dried with compressed air.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f3450010066" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd08/d0862.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Application of Loctite&#174; 620 Retaining Compound to glow plug sleeve</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Wall (end)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Upper wall (top)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply
                <hotlnk document="eges3451_237.xml" xrefid="s10.t3">Loctite&#174; 620 Retaining Compound</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s10.t3"/>
                to the wall and upper wall on glow plug sleeve.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3450010067" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM08/M08167.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Glow Plug Sleeve Installer ZTSE4532</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install glow plug sleeve in cylinder head with
                <hotlnk document="eges3451_237.xml" xrefid="s10.t3">Glow Plug Sleeve Installer ZTSE4532</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s10.t3"/>. Continue to tap the Glow Plug Sleeve Installer until the glow plug sleeve
                bottoms out in the recess.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clean glow plug sleeve with
                <hotlnk document="eges3451_237.xml" xrefid="s10.t3">Glow Plug Sleeve Brush (nylon) ZTSE4533</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s10.t3"/>
                and solvent. Make sure liquid gasket is cleaned out before it hardens.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the inside surface of the installed glow plug sleeve. If nicks and scratches are
                evident, replace the glow plug sleeve again. Make sure that the installation tool is not causing such
                damage. Use a different installation tool if necessary.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
